				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>You want to share your message with the world. You want to be heard. But in this day and age, with all the noise the Internet creates, building your platform can be challenging.</p>
<p><div id="attachment_15208" style="width: 640px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="http://goinswriter.com/wp-content/uploads/3342853636_d96c754ce6_b.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-15208" src="http://goinswriter.com/wp-content/uploads/3342853636_d96c754ce6_b-630x463.jpg" alt="030: Practical Strategies to Build Your Platform [Podcast]" width="630" height="463" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Photo Credit: <a href="https://www.flickr.com/photos/34883120@N02/3342853636/">skarpetka86</a> via <a href="http://compfight.com">Compfight</a> <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/2.0/">cc</a></p></div>In this episode of <a href="http://goinswriter.com/itunes" target="_blank">The Portfolio Life</a>, my co-host <a href="http://www.takepermission.com/" target="_blank">Andy Traub</a> and I discuss the five platform personalities and the reason they are so important.</p>
<p>We also talk about attracting attention to your work and the importance of relationships. And how offline connection leads to online influence.<br />
The way to build influence is one small interaction at a time and the key behind it all? Be thoughtful.</p>
<blockquote><p><em>If you want to connect with an influencer, don’t start with what you want, start with what they want. </em>[<a title="Tweet that" href="http://ctt.ec/ML9le" target="_blank">Tweet that</a>]</p></blockquote>
<p>As you listen to this week&#8217;s episode of the podcast, you&#8217;ll find practical strategies to build influence and grow your platform.</p>
